sogou-kaoyan.phr: (in the wake of)随...之后而来[出现2次)]
sogou-kaoyan.n: (wake-up call)让人警醒的事[出现1次)];(wakes)守护神节日[出现0次)]
sogou-kaoyan.v: 醒来; 引起; 激起[出现1次)];(wake up to)变得警觉[出现0次)]

sogou-gaokao.v: 醒; 醒来[出现8次)];叫醒; 吵醒[出现4次)];觉醒; 醒悟[出现0次)];苏醒; 活跃起来[出现0次)]

1.en: I began to start analyzing my situation to understand why I couldn't wake up early, through a self-questioning process.
1.cn: 于是我开始分析我的情况，通过自我反省找出到底为什么我早上没办法早起的原因。

2.en: You gotta wake up! 'I said, 'What happened, a minute ago I was a genius, and now I'm at the bottom of the pile?
2.cn: 我说：“一分钟之前我还是天才，现在怎么了就成了垫底的了呢？”

3.en: But the question of economic rationality has returned with a vengeance in the wake of the current crisis.
3.cn: 但在此次危机过后，经济理性的问题已卷土重来。

0.en: Please wake up, Hatter. Please. Wake up. Please wake up.
0.cn: 醒一醒，疯帽子，求你。醒来吧，求你醒醒吧。

1.en: And then wake up in the morning and do it some more.

2.en: So I wake up in my younger body, God knows where, then what?
2.cn: 我会在我年轻时的身体中醒来，鬼知那是哪，接着呢？

3.en: Then you can have a good night's rest and wake up tomorrow fresh on Abu Dhabi time.
3.cn: 之后您可以安睡一整晚，明天醒来神清气爽。

4.en: At least you get to wake up from your nightmare. I'm living with mine.
4.cn: 你起码可以从噩梦中醒来，我现在得一直生活在噩梦中。

5.en: Peppa and George have fallen to sleep. When they wake up, it will be Christmas day.
5.cn: 佩奇和乔治已经睡着了。等他们醒来就到圣诞节了。

6.en: Dreams make good stories, but everything important happens when we're wake.
6.cn: 梦境会编织骗人的幻象，可重要的事情都发生在醒来之后。

7.en: All right, gorgeous, you're back to the races. You're gonna wake in three, two, one.
7.cn: 好了，美人你可以回归赛场了，三、二、一 、醒来。

8.en: We can't do that, that's insane. I mean A: he could wake up and B: You know let's go for it.
8.cn: 不行，你疯了，第一，他可能醒来 第二，管他的。

9.en: But once you wake up, whatever you've done will take hold and become history.
9.cn: 但是，只要你一旦醒来，你所做的任何事都会固定下来，变成历史。

10.en: I'll do it. Sheldon, wait. You have to wake up first. Oh, of course. Set phasers to dumb, right?
10.cn: 我会这么做。谢尔顿，等等，你得先醒来。当然，先设好相位仪，对吧。

11.en: That's right, Dolores. You're in a dream. Would you like to wake up from this dream? Yes. I'm terrified.
11.cn: 没错，德洛丽丝，你在梦里，你想从梦里醒来吗？是的，我很害怕。

12.en: The bullet grazed his cortical shield. It's not pretty, but he should be functional. Wake up.
12.cn: 子弹擦过了他脑皮层表面，虽然挺严重，但是他应该还是可以运作的。醒来。

13.en: But then I would wake up and the voice would start all over again. So I ran away. Crossed the shining sea.
13.cn: 但接着我会醒来，这个声音再度响起，所以我逃跑了，越过大洋到达彼岸。

14.en: When I went under, the world was at war. I wake up. They say we won. They didn't say what we lost.
14.cn: 我昏过去的时候，这个世界在打仗。醒来以后听说我们赢了，不知道赢的代价是什么。

15.en: She's cold as ice. Ginny, please don't be dead. Wake up. You've got to help me, Tom. There's a basilisk.
15.cn: 她就跟冰块一样冷。金妮，求求你别死。快醒来。你必须帮帮我，汤姆。这里头有蛇怪。

16.en: I'd be trapped inside a huge egg and this monster would open his jaws and start to devour me. I'd wake up just in time.
16.cn: 梦见自己被困在巨型鸡蛋里，怪物张嘴将我吞入囊中，所幸每次都能及时醒来。

17.en: When I wake. What? That's the name of the song. Jackie Hill, July 17th, 1938, Bob Ellis on the drums.
17.cn: 当我醒来。什么？这首歌的名字，杰基·希尔，1938年7月17，鼓手是鲍勃·埃里森。

18.en: Good night, Peppa. Good night, George. Peppa and George have fallen to sleep. When they wake up, it will be Christmas day.
18.cn: 晚安了佩奇，晚安了，乔治。佩奇和乔治已经睡着了。等他们醒来就到圣诞节了。

19.en: If you wake up one morning with 1,000 times the strength you had the night before, how will you handle delicate day-to-day tasks?
19.cn: 如果某天早上你醒来发现你的力量是昨晚的一千倍，你该如何处理那些日常的精细活？
